---
description: Block any non-LLM network call, telemetry, or third-party SDK.
alwaysApply: true
---

# No third-party network calls

`epublatejs` is a static SPA. The only outbound request is the
user-configured OpenAI-compatible LLM endpoint. Everything else is a
**privacy regression**.

## Forbidden

- Telemetry / analytics SDKs (Sentry, PostHog, Datadog RUM, GA, …).
- Third-party fonts / CSS / scripts loaded from a CDN at runtime.
  Bundle assets locally.
- Auto-update channels, "phone home" version checks, crash reporters.
- Cloud sync of projects, glossaries, or LLM keys.
- New LLM provider SDKs that require their own HTTPS endpoint outside
  the user's configured base URL.

## When unsure

If a dependency might add a network call (analytics tracker baked in,
telemetry on by default), set up the integration in *off-by-default*
mode behind an explicit user opt-in **and** document the data flow in
`AGENTS.md`.

## Allowed

- The configured OpenAI-compatible endpoint, via `LLMProvider`.
- The configured OpenAI-compatible **embedding** endpoint, via
  `EmbeddingProvider` (re-uses the same base URL by default; can be
  pointed at a separate host through Settings → Embeddings).
- Embedding model weights from `huggingface.co/Xenova/*` after
  explicit per-project consent (see `EmbeddingProvider`'s `local`
  variant). Curators must click through the consent dialog once;
  weights are cached in the browser's Cache Storage and never
  re-fetched until they explicitly clear the cache.
- ONNX runtime WebAssembly artifacts from
  `cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@xenova/transformers/dist/*.wasm`. These are
  the runtime that executes the locally-downloaded weights and are
  pulled from the same source/version as the bundled npm package
  the consent screen references. They never carry user data and
  ride the consent gate.
- Service-worker / vite asset fetches at build time (compile to a
  static bundle).
- IndexedDB, localStorage, OPFS — fully local storage.

## Reviewer checklist

- [ ] No new `fetch(...)` outside `src/llm/`.
- [ ] No new `<script src=...>` tag pointing at a CDN.
- [ ] No new dependency that auto-instruments.
- [ ] No new analytics or telemetry imports.
- [ ] Local embedding download paths still gate on user consent.
